==English==

===Propwash Deflection Unit===
{{en-noun}}

# {{{1|{{A Propwash Deflection Unit, also known as a ''PDU'' or ''deflector'' is a device that is placed over or behind the propeller of a boat to deflect the vessel's propwash downward. The result is a very effective form of agitation dredging. PDUs are primarily used by salvors to remove mud or sand from shallow water shipwrecks.}}}}}

